DESCRIPTION
`etude run <workflow>` (live): walk an ARBITRARY stage graph in dependency order; resolve each stage's runner (registry name or inline; LLM or deterministic script) and invoke the external-runner contract (ETUDE_INPUTS_DIR/ETUDE_OUTPUT_FILE); run all stages in ONE evolving worktree per run; auto-generate run_id (timestamp+random, `--run-id` override, create-only); chain output role -> next input role per capture-run semantics; capture each stage INCREMENTALLY (compare-and-swap on the run ref) so `etude run show` works mid-run and a crash leaves a valid partial run; stop-and-capture on stage failure with `etude run --resume <id>`. Replay is redefined as FORWARD replay (stages 1..N). Design: docs/plans/product/live-execution.md S1.

DESIGN
## Plan — etude-xin: Live workflow orchestration (`etude run <workflow>`)

### Goal
Add a LIVE orchestrator: `etude run <workflow>` walks an arbitrary stage graph in
dependency order, resolves+invokes each stage's runner through the existing
external-runner contract (ETUDE_INPUTS_DIR/ETUDE_OUTPUT_FILE) in ONE evolving
worktree, chains output-role→input-role, and captures each stage INCREMENTALLY by
CAS-appending to refs/etude/runs/<id> so `etude run show` works mid-run and a
crash leaves a valid partial run. On stage failure: stop, leave the partial run,
resume with `--resume <id>`. Redefine `etude replay <run>` (no stage arg) as
FORWARD replay (stages 1..N). ORCHESTRATION ONLY.

