### Verified external behavior (cited, not assumed)
git 2.47.1, sha256 repo, reproduced in a throwaway `git init`:
- create-only: `git update-ref --no-deref <ref> <c0> ""` succeeds iff ref absent;
  re-running with old="" on an existing ref → `reference already exists`.
- CAS append: `commit-tree <tree> -p <c0>` + `update-ref --no-deref <ref> <c1> <c0>`
  succeeds; a stale old (c0 when head=c1) → `cannot lock ref ... but is at ... but
  expected ...`. This is exactly `refstore.WriteCommit` (ExpectedOld=""→create-only;
  non-empty→CAS-append-with-parent). Incremental capture rides this verbatim.
- `runmanifest.WriteManifestTree` rebuilds the FULL tree from `files` each call
  (writeTree → read-tree --empty), so every CAS-appended commit's tree is a
  COMPLETE, validated run snapshot. It validates manifest each call (≥1 stage), so
  the first write happens AFTER stage 0 completes.

### Approach — committed decisions (one per design question)

1. Incremental capture mechanism — CAS on the run ref.
   Maintain a single `*artifactstore.Store` across the run (accumulates every
   input+output blob) and a growing `[]runmanifest.Stage`. After EACH stage
   completes: append its Stage, build `runmanifest.Manifest{Stages: 0..i}`, call
   `runmanifest.WriteManifestTree(ctx, store, "refs/etude/runs/", manifest,
   files, refstore.WriteOptions{ExpectedOld: prevCommit, Message:...})`. Stage 0
   uses ExpectedOld="" (create-only → owns the run_id, errors ErrRefExists on
   collision). Stages 1..N use ExpectedOld=prevCommit (CAS append; a concurrent
   writer → ErrStaleRef → abort the run, partial run already durable). Track
   prevCommit from each write's returned OID. Stage-building is modelled on
   `replay/record.go` (build a Stage from result BYTES via artifactstore), not on
   capture_run.buildStage (which reads disk paths); the genuine shared core that
   both reuse is `runmanifest.WriteManifestTree` + `artifactstore` — no duplication
   of the validate→verify→write sequence.

2. Evolving worktree — one per run.
   The engine creates ONE worktree via `worktree.Checkout(ctx, root, runGitSHA)`
   (runGitSHA = HEAD at start, or `--git-sha`), owns it for the whole run, and
   `defer wt.Close()`. Every stage runs with cwd=wt.Dir, so git-lifecycle stages
   (`git checkout -b`) and deterministic stages reading earlier mutations Just
   Work. Inter-stage DATA flows two ways: (a) role chaining via captured artifacts
   (materialized into scratch ETUDE_INPUTS_DIR), and (b) worktree mutations shared
   in place. For replay hermeticity, the contract is that any state a later stage
   needs is either captured as a chained artifact role OR re-derivable by re-running
   deterministic stages in the evolving worktree (see decision 6).

3. run_id generation.
   `<workflow>-<UTC:20060102T150405Z>-<4-byte crypto/rand hex>` (sortable by
   timestamp, satisfies IsValidRunID: charset ok, no `..`/leading/trailing dot/
   `.lock`). `--run-id` overrides (validated via runmanifest.IsValidRunID).
   Create-only is enforced structurally by stage-0's ExpectedOld="" write — an
   explicit collision returns the same friendly "already exists" message
   capture_run uses. (Do NOT use replay.AllocateRunID — its -2..-10 suffix probing
   is replay-collision behavior, wrong for create-only live runs.)

4. Runner resolution.
   New helper `resolveStageRunner(wf, reg, stage) (*replay.ExecRunner, error)`:
   pick `stage.Runner` else `wf.DefaultRunner` else error (no runner). If
   `.Command != ""` → ExecRunner{Command: strings.Fields(command)}. If
   `.Name != ""` → look up `reg.Seats[name]` (error if undefined) → ExecRunner{
   Command: strings.Fields(seat.Invoke)}. Timeout from `--timeout`, MaxOutputBytes
   64<<20 (mirror replay.go). LLM vs deterministic script are both just commands —
   no special-casing. This is the cross-file resolution deferred from 2pc.1.

5. Stop-and-capture + resume.
   On a stage runner returning non-zero/timeout (ExecRunner already maps these to
   ErrRunnerFailed / DeadlineExceeded): STOP. The partial run = all stages already
   CAS-captured (durable). `etude run` exits non-zero and prints `stage <name>
   failed: <err>` + `resume with: etude run <workflow> --resume <id>` on stderr.
   `--resume <id>`: load the run manifest, build the set of completed Produces
   roles, derive the frontier = first workflow stage whose Produces role is not yet
   present (the cold-etude "diff produced vs workflow" model — no stored current
   stage). Re-seed the artifactstore by iterating the manifest's REFERENCED ARTIFACT
   PATHS — every captured stage's INPUTS *and* OUTPUTS (runmanifest.ArtifactPaths) —
   reading each blob's bytes back from the run commit (ReadCommitFile/ReadFile ->
   artifactstore.AddContent), NOT just outputs and NOT just the role->ArtifactRef
   map — because WriteManifestTree rebuilds the full tree from `files` and
   verifyArtifactFile requires every referenced artifact present in `files`; an
   outputs-only/refs-only reseed makes the first post-resume CAS append fail with
   ErrMissingArtifact (opus catch). IMPORTANT: the `task` special-role input blob
   must be reseeded from the commit too — on `--resume`, `--task` is ignored (id
   comes from the arg), so stage-0's task input is available only from the captured
   run; iterating referenced paths covers it. Re-open ONE worktree at the run's
   recorded git_sha READ FROM THE MANIFEST (do NOT recompute HEAD, so a moved HEAD
   between the failed run and the resume cannot silently change the worktree base),
   then continue CAS-appending from prevCommit=current ref head. Plain stages never
   auto-retry.
   SCOPE NARROWING (gate round 1): a durable "failed stage status" record and its
   surfacing in `run show` are OUT OF SCOPE for etude-xin and tracked in **etude-dp7**
   (filed, depends on etude-xin). AC3 requires only resumability, which the
   frontier-by-diff mechanism delivers without a failed-status field (a failed stage
   produces no output, so the frontier lands exactly on it). Failure is surfaced
   live via nonzero exit + stderr only.

6. Forward replay — `etude replay <run>` (stage arg becomes optional).
   Today `etude replay <run> <stage>` (ExactArgs(2)) replays ONE stage: resolve
   recorded inputs → checkout recorded git_sha → run runner → emit/optionally
   --record a linked run. Minimal change: relax to `cobra.RangeArgs(1,2)`. With a
   stage arg → unchanged single-stage behavior. With NO stage arg → FORWARD replay:
   create ONE evolving worktree at the run's git_sha, then for each stage in
   manifest order materialize THAT stage's RECORDED (content-addressed) inputs into
   scratch and re-invoke its runner with cwd=the shared evolving worktree, emitting
   each stage's output. Forward + one-evolving-worktree replaces the per-stage
   pristine random-access model (spec decision 5); hermeticity holds because every
   stage's INPUTS are the captured artifacts (drift in one stage never propagates
   to the next). Deterministic runners reproduce worktree state exactly (the
   proof). LLM-stage output SUBSTITUTION (trusting recorded output over re-invoking
   a non-deterministic model) is explicitly deferred to the dev-workflow migration
   (2pc.2); v1 re-invokes runners forward, which is exact for deterministic graphs.

### Chaining + contract details
- `--task <file>` seeds the special role `task`. Special role `repo-state` is
  implicit = the cwd worktree (NOT materialized into the inputs dir, NOT recorded
  as an ArtifactRef — it is captured by the stage's git_sha). All other stage
  Inputs resolve from a role→(ArtifactRef,bytes) map of previously-produced
  outputs; each stage registers its Produces output into that map. workflow.Validate
  already guarantees every input is special-or-produced-earlier.
- Per stage: materialize chained inputs to <scratch>/inputs/NN-role (reuse
  ExecRunner which does this), invoke, read output, store output bytes via
  artifactstore (role = stage.Produces), append Stage, CAS-write.
- Producer/skill: Stage.Skill + Producer.Skill = {ID: stage.Skill, Repo/Version:
  default "manual"/run-level} so validateStage passes; Producer.Harness/Model left
  empty (valid) — populated later by 2pc.2. ProducedBy="original". GitSHA=runGitSHA.
  Workflow/WorkflowVersion = wf.Name / "<name>-v1".

